      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain, then add your <strong>king</strong> <strong>prawns</strong> and cook for 3-4 min</p><p>Add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan with your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[62ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span> of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
